## SECTION 3: RUNTIME HEADER (freak_runtime.h)

The transpiler emits `#include "freak_runtime.h"` at the top of every C file.
This header provides all FREAK's built-in types and operations.

### 3.1 word type

```c
typedef struct {
    const char* data;
    size_t length;      // byte length
    size_t char_count;  // codepoint count
} freak_word;

freak_word freak_word_lit(const char* s);        // from string literal
freak_word freak_word_concat(freak_word a, freak_word b);
freak_word freak_word_slice(freak_word w, size_t from, size_t to);
bool freak_word_eq(freak_word a, freak_word b);
bool freak_word_contains(freak_word w, freak_word needle);
freak_word freak_word_from_int(int64_t n);
freak_word freak_word_from_double(double n);
freak_word freak_interpolate(const char* fmt, ...);  // handles {x} substitution
const char* freak_word_to_cstr(freak_word w);
```

### 3.2 say and I/O

```c
void freak_say(freak_word msg);           // print with newline
void freak_say_err(freak_word msg);       // stderr
freak_word freak_ask(freak_word prompt);  // read line from stdin
```

### 3.3 List<T>

In FREAK Lite, List<T> is implemented as a type-erased dynamic array.
Use void* with element size, or generate typed list structs per T.

Recommended: generate typed structs per concrete T used.

```c
// Generated for List<int>:
typedef struct {
    int64_t* data;
    size_t length;
    size_t capacity;
} freak_list_int;

freak_list_int freak_list_int_new();
void freak_list_int_push(freak_list_int* list, int64_t val);
freak_maybe_int freak_list_int_get(freak_list_int* list, size_t i);
int64_t freak_list_int_get_unsafe(freak_list_int* list, size_t i); // list[i] syntax
void freak_list_int_free(freak_list_int* list);
// ... filter, map, fold, etc. take function pointers + env pointers
```

