## SECTION 4: WHAT FREAK LITE INCLUDES vs EXCLUDES

### INCLUDED in FREAK Lite v1

- All primitive types (num, int, uint, tiny, float, float32, word, bool, char, void)
- Fixed arrays [T; N]
- Tuples (A, B)
- maybe<T> and result<T, E>
- List<T>, Map<K, V>, Set<T>, Lineup<T>
- pilot variable declarations
- task functions (all forms: block, done, arrow)
- shape structs + impl blocks
- doctrine traits + impl for
- Generics with doctrine bounds
- if/else, when, for each, repeat, training arc
- Destructuring
- Closures and lambdas (all capture modes)
- Pipe operator |>
- ? error propagation
- give back, say (keyword)
- String interpolation
- Modules and imports (use, launch)
- trust me blocks (no enforcement, just C block)
- Anime keywords: @protagonist, @nakige, @side_character, @experiment, @fixed_fate
- Anime call keywords: knowing this will hurt, sadly, for science
- foreshadow/payoff (compile-time tracking)
- route return type (tagged enum)
- training arc loop
- Anime operators: PLUS ULTRA, NAKAMA, FINAL FORM, TSUNDERE
- mood type (enum, no compound logic in Lite v1)
- Basic test blocks (compile to no-ops in release, simple assertions in test mode)

### EXCLUDED from FREAK Lite v1 (add in v2+)

- Full borrow checker (lend/lend mut parsed but not enforced)
- power<N> type (compile-time power levels)
- prob[range] type (probability distributions)
- causality<T> type (cross-timeline values)
- xm3 {} concurrency blocks
- Squadron concurrency (sortie, formation, debrief, comms, briefing room, wingman)
- direct_order inline assembly
- deus_ex_machina block
- @season_finale annotation
- @rival annotation
- @classified annotation
- Mood compound arithmetic
- Route-locked variables (only on route X)
- Timeline diff / declare X was T in timeline N
- isekai block
- eventually block
- Causality conductor type
- big arbitrary precision integers
- SIMD operations (math::simd)
- Full borrow checker and lifetime analysis

