    UNDERSCORE = "_"
```

### 6.2 Lexer Notes

- Comments: `--` to end of line. Skip entirely.
- Strings: `"..."` with `{expr}` interpolation markers — lex the whole string as STRING_LIT, track interpolation spans separately
- Multi-word tokens: `give back`, `or else`, `trust me`, `training arc`, `on my honor as`, `for each`, `knowing this will hurt`, `for science`, `PLUS ULTRA`, `FINAL FORM` — lex greedily when the first word matches
- `done` closes blocks only when on its own line or followed by newline — treat like `}`
- Annotations `@protagonist` etc: lex `@` then IDENT
- Number suffixes: `42u` → uint, `3.14f` → float32, `42t` → tiny, `999b` → big (skip big in Lite v1)
- Semicolons optional — never required, skip them

