## SECTION 9: C EMITTER — ORDERING RULES

The C emitter must output declarations in this order to avoid forward reference issues:

1. `#include "freak_runtime.h"`
2. All `typedef struct` for shapes (topologically sorted by dependency)
3. All `typedef struct` for generated types (maybe, result, list, closure envs)
4. All function forward declarations (so mutual recursion works)
5. All function definitions
6. `int main(int argc, char** argv) { return freak_main(); }`

