## SECTION 11: OPUS API INTEGRATION POINTS

Call the Opus API for these specific tasks during compilation:

### 11.1 Death Flag Detection (@side_character)

When a @side_character variable is involved in a statement, send the AST node to Opus
and ask: "Does this code trigger any death flags? Respond with JSON: {flags: [], severity: 0-4}"
Severity 1-2: emit warning. Severity 3-4: emit error (user can override with @i_know_what_im_doing).

### 11.2 Narrative Error Messages

When any compile error occurs, optionally call Opus to generate a character-voiced version.
Send: error type, details, voice setting (from hangar.toml or --voice flag).
Use the raw error if Opus call fails or is slow.

### 11.3 freak vibe Command

When user runs `freak vibe`, send entire source to Opus.
Ask: "Analyze this FREAK code for narrative quality, power level distribution, death flag density,
foreshadowing completion rate, and emotional coherence. Return a vibe report."

### 11.4 Caching

Cache all Opus API responses keyed by (hash of input, prompt type).
Avoid redundant API calls for unchanged code.

